            Blackstone Inc. has <a href="https://www.bnnbloomberg.ca/investing/2024/10/01/blackstone-leads-private-credit-deal-for-anti-theft-tech-maker/" target="_blank">closed</a> a $550 million private credit deal with Graham Partners Inc.’s Gatekeeper Systems, a shopping cart anti-theft tech maker. The deal includes a dividend and portability feature, allowing flexibility for future mergers, acquisitions, or sales. This move boosts Gatekeeper’s growth potential, giving the company more options to expand. Private credit deals with portability features have become increasingly common as sponsors look to streamline transactions.
          </p>
